The paper discusses the population genetics of evolution in the context of coordination games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the study of equilibria and dynamics, which are topics in both evolutionary computation (cs.EC) and dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper also uses mathematical techniques such as linear algebra and probability theory, which are relevant to both machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
